  "text": "One mechanism that can explain the imperfect linkage disequilibrium between the deletion and the neighboring variants can be recurrent formation of deletions. In other words, if two or more independent deletion events have occurred in different haplotypic backgrounds, then we expect (i) different deletion breakpoints, and (ii) LD to be intact between the variants on each side of the deletion as described by Boettger et al. [CITATION_1] . In a previous study, we conducted an analysis of the breakpoints of this deletion, but, due to repetitive nature of this locus, could not identify the exact breakpoints of this deletion [CITATION_2] . In parallel, we found that there is relatively weak, but observable linkage disequilibrium (R 2 =$0.5) between variants on each side of the deletion in CHB ( Figure 2C ). Overall, our results cannot rule out recurrent formation of the GSTM1 deletion in the human lineage.",
